Sally has 3 brothers. Her brothers have 2 sisters. How many sisters does Sally have? Explain your answer
If Sally has 3 brothers and her brothers have 2 sisters, then the total number of siblings (brothers + sisters) that Sally has is:
Number of brothers + Number of sisters = 1 + 2 = 3
So, Sally has 3 brothers and 2 sisters. Therefore, she has a total of 5 siblings.
